==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Necessitarianism
<hw>Ne*ces`si*ta"ri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
doctrine of philosophical necessity; the doctrine that results follow by
invariable sequence from causes, and esp. that the will is not free, but
that human actions and choices result inevitably from motives;
determinism.</def> <rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necessitate</ent>⟦br⟧
